.TH HARDLINE 1 "June 2026" "hardline 1.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hardline \- dependency-free Linux hardening auditor
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hardline
.RB [ \-\-json ]
.RB [ \-\-quiet ]
.RB [ \-\-no\-color ]
.br
.B hardline
.RB [ \-h | \-\-help ]
.RB [ \-V | \-\-version ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hardline
is a single bash script that runs roughly forty read-only checks across SSH,
kernel sysctls, the firewall, accounts and sudo, the filesystem, and services,
then prints a colored report and a letter grade.
.PP
It only reads. It never edits a config, restarts a service, or contacts the
network. Each finding points you at what to look at; the fix stays your call.
A handful of checks (the empty-password scan, NOPASSWD sudo rules, the full
sshd configuration) need root to read their source files \(em without
.BR sudo (8)
they report
.B SKIP
rather than a misleading
.BR PASS .
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-json
Emit machine-readable JSON instead of the human report: an object with
.IR score ", " grade ", the " pass / warn / fail / skip " counts, and a " checks
array. Ideal for CI and dashboards.
.TP
.B \-\-quiet
Suppress
.B PASS
and
.B SKIP
lines; show only
.BR WARN ", " FAIL ", and the summary."
.TP
.B \-\-no\-color
Strip ANSI escape sequences. Applied automatically when stdout is not a TTY.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print a short usage summary and exit.
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Print the version and exit.
.SH "GRADING"
The score is
.RI ( PASS " + " WARN "\(mu0.5) / total" .
Letter grades run from F to A+, and any single
.B FAIL
caps the grade at C \(em one open door undoes a lot of good locks.
.B SKIP
results do not count against the score.
.SH "EXIT STATUS"
.TP
.B 0
No
.B FAIL
results.
.TP
.B 1
One or more checks failed.
.TP
.B 2
Usage error (unknown option).
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Audit the current host as root for the fullest coverage:
.B sudo hardline
.TP
Fail a CI job on any finding and capture the report:
.B hardline \-\-json | jq \-e '.fail == 0'
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR lynis (8),
.BR sshd_config (5),
.BR sysctl (8)
.PP
